<speak version="1.0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/10/synthesis" xmlns:mstts="https://www.w3.org/2001/mstts" xml:lang="en-IN"><voice name="en-IN-Diya:DragonHDLatestNeural" parameters="temperature=0.55"><break time="700ms"/><mstts:express-as style="calm" styledegree="0.4"><prosody rate="-1%"><p>This source paragraph is intentionally too long for its tiny transport limit.</p></prosody></mstts:express-as></voice></speak>
<speak version="1.0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/10/synthesis" xmlns:mstts="https://www.w3.org/2001/mstts" xml:lang="en-IN"><voice name="en-IN-Diya:DragonHDLatestNeural" parameters="temperature=0.55"><break time="180ms"/><mstts:express-as style="calm" styledegree="0.4"><prosody rate="-1%"><p>It contains several complete sentences, but the renderer must reject it instead of converting those sentences into independently paced paragraphs.</p></prosody></mstts:express-as></voice></speak>
<speak version="1.0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/10/synthesis" xmlns:mstts="https://www.w3.org/2001/mstts" xml:lang="en-IN"><voice name="en-IN-Diya:DragonHDLatestNeural" parameters="temperature=0.55"><break time="180ms"/><mstts:express-as style="calm" styledegree="0.4"><prosody rate="-1%"><p>The author must decide where the thought genuinely changes.</p></prosody></mstts:express-as></voice></speak>
